<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Banff 40th | May 28–31</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;0,900;1,400&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400;500&family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;1,300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --linen:      #f6f2eb;
    --linen-dk:   #ede8de;
    --forest:     #1e4230;
    --forest-lt:  #2d6147;
    --teal:       #2a7a6a;
    --teal-lt:    #3a9a86;
    --sky:        #2e5f7a;
    --sky-lt:     #3a7a9a;
    --slate:      #5a6a72;
    --slate-lt:   #7a8a92;
    --orange:     #c05a20;
    --orange-lt:  #d47040;
    --ink:        #1a2420;
    --ink-mid:    #2e3c36;
    --rule:       rgba(30,66,48,0.15);
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: var(--linen);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    min-height: 100vh;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 420px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    justify-content: center;
    background: #a8c8d8;
  }

  .hero-photo {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center 55%;
  }

  .hero svg.scene {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  /* Gradient overlay: dark at bottom so text reads */
  .hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.0) 0%,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.05) 50%,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.52) 80%,
      rgba(8,20,14,0.78) 100%
    );
  }

  .hero-text {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 36px;
    padding-left: 16px;
    padding-right: 16px;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.38em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s 0.3s forwards;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(46px, 9vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1;
    color: #ffffff;
    text-shadow: 0 3px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.55), 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s 0.5s forwards;
  }
  .hero-title em { font-style: italic; color: #f0c080; }

  .hero-sub {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.88);
    text-shadow: 0 1px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    margin-top: 10px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s 0.7s forwards;
  }

  .hero-credit {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 8px;
    right: 12px;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  /* ── FLIGHTS BAR ── */
  .flights-bar {
    background: var(--forest);
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--teal);
    padding: 14px 20px;
  }
  .flights-inner { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .flights-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .flight-group {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 5px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .flight-group:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .fg-time   { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: #f0c080; min-width: 68px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .fg-flight { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: #7eb8d4; min-width: 80px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .fg-names  { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif; font-size: 15px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }

  /* ── MAIN LAYOUT ── */
  .container { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px 64px; }

  .section-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 22px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(42,122,106,0.4), transparent);
  }

  /* Day blocks */
  .day { margin-bottom: 48px; opacity: 0; animation: fadeIn 0.6s forwards; }
  .day:nth-child(1){animation-delay:0.1s}
  .day:nth-child(2){animation-delay:0.2s}
  .day:nth-child(3){animation-delay:0.3s}
  .day:nth-child(4){animation-delay:0.4s}
  @keyframes fadeIn { to { opacity: 1; } }

  .day-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--rule);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .day-name {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--forest);
  }
  .day-date {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--teal);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  }
  .day-tag {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--teal);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* Events */
  .events { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .event {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 72px 1fr;
    gap: 0 16px;
    padding: 12px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .event:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .event-time {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--sky);
    padding-top: 3px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .event-name {
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .event-detail {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--slate);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .badges { margin-top: 5px; display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .event-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .badge-booked   { background: rgba(42,122,106,0.12); color: var(--teal);    border: 1px solid rgba(42,122,106,0.35); }
  .badge-suggest  { background: rgba(46,95,122,0.10);  color: var(--sky);     border: 1px solid rgba(46,95,122,0.3); }
  .badge-optional { background: rgba(90,106,114,0.10); color: var(--slate);   border: 1px solid rgba(90,106,114,0.25); }
  .badge-warn     { background: rgba(192,90,32,0.12);  color: var(--orange);  border: 1px solid rgba(192,90,32,0.35); }

  /* Hien quote box */
  .hien-box {
    background: var(--linen-dk);
    border: 1px solid rgba(42,122,106,0.2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }
  .hien-label {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 7px;
  }
  .hien-box p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--slate); font-style: italic; line-height: 1.65; }

  /* Divider */
  .divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--rule), transparent);
    margin: 38px 0;
  }

  /* Tips */
  .tips {
    padding: 26px 28px;
    background: var(--linen-dk);
    border: 1px solid rgba(30,66,48,0.12);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--forest);
    border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
  }
  .tips h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .tip-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
  .tip-item { display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .tip-icon { font-size: 15px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--slate); line-height: 1.55; }
  .tip-text strong { color: var(--ink-mid); }

  .footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 24px;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: var(--slate-lt);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .tip-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .event { grid-template-columns: 58px 1fr; }
    .hero { height: 340px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HERO: Lake Louise in late May — inline SVG so it always renders -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-photo" style="background-image:url('data:image/jpeg;base64,');"></div>

  <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
  <div class="hero-text">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">6 of the guys · Banff, Alberta</div>
    <div class="hero-title">The <em>Forty</em></div>
    <div class="hero-sub">May 28 – 31, 2025 · Happy Birthday, Mike</div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-credit">Lake Louise, late May · Banff National Park</div>
</div>

<!-- FLIGHTS BAR -->
<div class="flights-bar">
  <div class="flights-inner">
    <div class="flights-label">✈ Arrivals — Thursday May 28 · Calgary YYC</div>
    <div class="flight-group">
      <div class="fg-time">11:03 AM</div>
      <div class="fg-flight">WestJet 1024</div>
      <div class="fg-names">John Byun</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flight-group">
      <div class="fg-time">11:04 AM</div>
      <div class="fg-flight">Delta</div>
      <div class="fg-names">Phil Jung</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flight-group">
      <div class="fg-time">12:24 PM</div>
      <div class="fg-flight">UA 286</div>
      <div class="fg-names">Michael Hwang · Jorge Rincon · Ro Samahon · Brian Park</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">

  <!-- ══ THURSDAY ══ -->
  <div class="day">
    <div class="section-label">Day 1</div>
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-name">Thursday</div>
      <div class="day-date">MAY 28</div>
      <div class="day-tag">Arrival</div>
    </div>
    <div class="events">

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">11 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">John &amp; Phil Land at YYC</div>
          <div class="event-detail">First two in — head to baggage claim and wait for the UA crew arriving at 12:24.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">12:24 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Mike, Jorge, Ro &amp; Brian Land — UA 286</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Full crew assembled. Head to ground transportation together.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">1:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Pick Up Rental Car — Hertz YYC</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Car reserved at 1:30 PM. ~1 hr 20 min drive to Banff from the airport.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ Reserved</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~2 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Costco Run — West Calgary</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Stock up on drinks, snacks, and breakfast food on the way out. Costco sits right on the Trans-Canada corridor heading to Banff.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~3:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Drive to Banff — Trans-Canada Hwy</div>
          <div class="event-detail">~1 hr 20 min. The Rockies appear fast — stay awake for it.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">5:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Check In — 129 Muskrat St, Banff</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Drop bags, unload the Costco haul, pick rooms. Downtown Banff — everything is walkable.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ Booked</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">6 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Drinks at the Airbnb</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Crack open the Costco supply. Settle in, no need to rush out tonight.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">7:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Dinner — Tooloulou's or Elk + Oat</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Both walkable downtown. Tooloulou's for Cajun comfort and big group energy; Elk + Oat for craft beer and elevated pub fare. Walk-in friendly on Thursdays.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-suggest">Suggested</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">9 PM+</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Nightcap — Rose &amp; Crown or Hoodoo Lounge</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Keep it reasonable — early shuttle tomorrow morning at 8:20.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ══ FRIDAY ══ -->
  <div class="day">
    <div class="section-label">Day 2</div>
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-name">Friday</div>
      <div class="day-date">MAY 29</div>
      <div class="day-tag">Lake Louise</div>
    </div>
    <div class="events">

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">Morning</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Breakfast at the Airbnb</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Quick breakfast from Costco supplies. Coffee and get moving — early start today.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">8:00 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Walk to Banff High School Transit Hub</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Leave the Airbnb by 8:00 AM to make the bus. Short walk from downtown.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">8:20 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Shuttle Departs → Lake Louise</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Parks Canada shuttle from Banff High School Transit Hub. Arrive Lake Louise lakeshore ~9:00 AM. Bring layers — colder at elevation. <strong>Mike has the tickets.</strong></div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ Booked · Mike has tickets</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">9–11 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Lake Louise Lakeshore Walk</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Early morning before crowds arrive — glacier reflecting off still water. Walk the full lakeshore (5 km return). Possibly the most iconic view in Canada.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">11 AM–2 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Hike — Plain of Six Glaciers or Big Beehive</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Plain of Six Glaciers (14 km, moderate) ends at a historic teahouse with glacier views. Big Beehive (11 km) gives a bird's-eye view back down to the lake. Both have breathtaking scenery.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-suggest">Choose one</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~1–2 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Lunch — Pack it or Fairmont Chateau</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Either pack lunch from the Airbnb or grab post-hike food and beers at the Fairview Bar inside the Chateau Lake Louise.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">3:20 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Head to Lake Louise Bus Stop</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Be at the lakeshore bus area by 3:20 for the 3:44 PM shuttle back to Banff.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ 3:44 shuttle home</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~5 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Back at Airbnb — Rest &amp; Get Ready</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Freshen up before dinner.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">6:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Dinner — Good Folk</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Reservation under Michael Hwang. </div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ Booked · Res: Michael Hwang</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">8:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Banff Night Sky — Northern Lights &amp; Stargazing Tour</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Guided dark-sky experience out of town. Late May is prime aurora season in the Rockies. Download My Aurora Forecast to check conditions the day before — decide whether to keep or cancel. <strong>Mike has the tickets.</strong></div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">✓ Booked (cancellable) · Mike has tickets</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="hien-box">
      <div class="hien-label">💬 From Hien — visited end of May</div>
      <p>"There are tons of trails for hiking with the most breathtaking scenery. It was one of my best trips — hope you all enjoy it."</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ══ SATURDAY ══ -->
  <div class="day">
    <div class="section-label">Day 3</div>
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-name">Saturday</div>
      <div class="day-date">MAY 30</div>
      <div class="day-tag">Johnston Canyon &amp; Upper Hot Springs</div>
    </div>
    <div class="events">

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">8:15 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Breakfast at the Airbnb</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Coffee, easy breakfast, pack layers, swim trunks, and water for the hike.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">9:00 AM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Drive to Johnston Canyon</div>
          <div class="event-detail">~30 min from 129 Muskrat St via Trans-Canada Hwy (Hwy 1) to Castle Junction, then 7 km east on Hwy 1A to the trailhead. Note: Bow Valley Parkway is closed to vehicles Mar 1–Jun 25 — Hwy 1 is the only route.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">9:30 AM–12 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Hike — Johnston Canyon to Upper Falls</div>
          <div class="event-detail">5 km return with spectacular catwalks through the canyon. Lower Falls at 1.2 km, Upper Falls at 2.5 km. Get there early — it fills up by mid-morning. 2–2.5 hrs at a relaxed pace.</div>
          <div class="badges"><span class="event-badge badge-booked">On the plan</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">12–1 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Lunch — Blackswift Bistro at the Trailhead</div>
          <div class="event-detail">No need to drive back to Banff — there's a café and bistro right at the Johnston Canyon trailhead. Grab food and drinks here before heading to the springs. Seasonal hours (open in summer).</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">1:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Drive to Banff Upper Hot Springs</div>
          <div class="event-detail">~35 min from Johnston Canyon back via Hwy 1 east toward Banff, then up Sulphur Mountain Rd. Arrive ~1:45 PM — springs open at 1:00 PM, first come first serve.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~1:45 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Banff Upper Hot Springs</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Tickets are in-person only (no online booking) and can sell out on busy Saturdays — worth arriving without too much delay. Historic mineral springs at 37–40°C with a panoramic view of Mount Rundle. Perfect post-hike soak. Plan for 1.5–2 hrs.</div>
          <div class="badges">
            <span class="event-badge badge-warn">In-person only · May sell out</span>
            <span class="event-badge badge-suggest">$19.75 CAD / person</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">~3:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-name">Drive Back to Airbnb</div>
